for giving renjuclass such a long life.
shakes hands with  some Irish beer to everyone
As you know, all of the staff members have worked so hard,
giving their free time and energy to serve you all
We are all thankful to them.

and helping to build this community even bigger and better as it was before.

being the headmaster of renju department,
lu not the longest but best
working with administration tools and more more.

maybe we'll meet togeather next Sunday somewhere in London? :)

teacher is playing the moves for one side,
and students play as a team for the other side,
the move is chosen by votes
the move that gets most votes, will be submitted by students representative
all the IDs except guests have the right to vote
all kinds of discussion is allowed.
feel free to persuade each other
yes, we play to learn first, then second, play to win
now, we need to select someone, who will play the moves and count the votes
do not spend more than 1 minute on discussion
and remember, do not vote twice!
if you just type a coordinate without any text, such as "h5", it is considered as a vote
so , if your intention is to discuss,
then say something more than a coordinate
such as "i think h5 is good"
if you only say a coordinate, its a VOTE
and you can only vote once per each move

please do not vote two times

if someone voted, then the vote stays
the first steps are always fast
i guess people are so confident
the voting may begin even after 1 minute of discussion
you have 1 minute for discussion, and then fast voting
we have a minute for discussion, then we can vote :P
we can use rt time to comment too :P
whether you win or not, depends entirely on your teamwork!!
